it.emarolab.owloop.aMORDescriptor

Interface MORAxioms

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Semantic

    public interface MORAxioms
extends Semantic
    The main interface for Semantic.Axioms implemented in the aMOR API.

    This interface contains all the Axioms, SemanticAxiom and SemanticAxioms used in the Concept, Individual, DataProperty and ObjectProperty Descriptors for the OWLOOP architecture implemented with the aMOR framework.
    All of those manage a collection of ontological entities, eventually attached with a specific semantic. In particular all are based on MORAxioms.AxiomsBase, which implements the management of an HashSet with a specified type. When the type is an OWLObject, the MORAxioms.OWLAxiomsBase in used just to extend the MORAxioms.AxiomsBase.toString() method.
    More in particular, the implemented axioms set are:

    • MORAxioms.Individuals: for describing a set of ontological individuals.
    • MORAxioms.Concepts: for describing a set of ontological classes.
    • MORAxioms.Literals: for describing a set of ontological data values (used by the MORAxioms.DataSemantic axiom implementation).
    • MORAxioms.DataLinks: for describing a set of ontological data properties.
    • MORAxioms.ObjectLinks: for describing a set of ontological object properties.
    • MORAxioms.Restrictions: for describing a set of restriction (i.e.: for concept definition as wel as data and property range or domain definition).
    • MORAxioms.DataSemantic: for describing a set of data values with a semantic (i.e.: by MORAxioms.DataSemantics).
    • MORAxioms.ObjectSemantic: for describing a set of data values with a semantic (i.e.: by MORAxioms.ObjectSemantics).
